                "deathNote": true,
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A clockwork dragon must use this reaction unless specifically programmed otherwise by its creator</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The clockwork dragon is reduced to 0 Hit Points</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The dragon screeches to a stop and emits a steady, loud ticking sound. At the beginning of what would have been its next turn, the dragon explodes, dealing [[/r {12d10}[piercing]]]{12d10 piercing damage} in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:40] (@Check[type:reflex|dc:37|basic:true] save).</p>\n<p>An adjacent creature can cancel the self-destruct sequence by succeeding at a @Check[type:thievery|dc:37|name:Cancel Self-Destruct|traits:action:disable-device] check to Disable a Device.</p>"
